OL,3,CGovernment considers welfare reform
OL,4,Cconcessions as Labour MPs threaten to
OL,5,Crevolt
OL,7,FAccording to the Government's own
OL,8,Ffigures, the welfare cuts will push
OL,9,F250,000 people into poverty, including
OL,10,F50,000 children. Given that ministers
OL,11,Fare already working on a child poverty
OL,12,Fstrategy, one option could be to
OL,13,Fexpedite some of those changes.
OL,15,FMPs are also pressing ministers to set
OL,16,Fout details about a promise to provide
OL,17,Fa disability "premium" to the most
OL,18,Fseverely disabled.
